BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260519T101200
DTEND:20260519T124800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.051ft at 10:12\n-2.925ft at 12:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Fresh combo of building long-period WNW swell and new small S swell - the 
 WNW swell will be dominant for most spots. The mix looks good for widespre
 ad waist-chest-shoulder high waves by the afternoon\, as better breaks are
  about head high. \n\nDraining negative low tide first part of the morning
 \, then incoming tide push helps through mid day. Early afternoon high tid
 e slows tide sensitive spots. Light/variable winds through the morning\, e
 xpected to turn light+ SW for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
