BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260520T110000
DTEND:20260520T134800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.036ft at 11:00\n-2.996ft at 13:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 WNW swell eases\, most breaks down a notch from Tuesday as the swell perio
 d comes down. S swell up a bit more.  End result is mainly waist-chest hig
 h+ surf\, while best combo spots push head high. \n\nDraining negative low
  tide first half of the morning\, then incoming tide push helps into the e
 arly afternoon. Mid afternoon high tide bog down tide sensitive breaks. Li
 ght/variable morning winds\, followed by light+ SW afternoon onshores. 
END:VEVENT
